  <description>
  <![CDATA[
<div>
<h1><i>JCaptcha is an open source JAVA framework to help to create captchas</i>.</h1>

<div class='indent'>
captchas, for Completely Automated Public Test to tell Humans and Computers Apart, are tests based on several cognitives puzzles based on challenging problems of artificial intelligence.
<br />
</div>
These tests are to prevent computer programs or robots to obtain information, by challenging with a problem that only human can resolve.
</div>
<br />
<div>
<b>Jcaptcha</b> is divided into three main features:
<ul>
<li>The <b>JcaTchaCore</b> Framework, which help to create captchas,
</li>
<li>The <b>JcaTchaJ2ee</b> Integration, which provides two components, the <b>ImagecaptchaFilter</b> and the <b>Imagecaptchaservlet</b> designed to integrate <b>Jcaptcha</b> to your Java Web Application,
</li>
<li>Some <b>JcaTchaSamples</b> to help developers to create captchas in command line programs or in web applications.
<br />
</li>
</ul>
This picture show you an overview of Jcaptcha:
</div>
<br />
<div>
<img alt='BIG PICTURE' src='images/big_picture2.jpg' />
</div>
<br />
<br />
<div>
Jcaptcha is free and released under open-source <b>Apache License</b>.
</div>
  ]]>
